    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-09-28T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-09-28T14:00:00-05:00" n="319"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d319">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/3334: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Feely</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-09-28T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 28, 1933—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:11 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>75. The Brazilian Minister of Foreign Affairs today informed the Bolivian
                    Government that if the ABCP is to accept the League mandate Bolivia must either
                    accept without reservation the proposal of August 25th or the Chilean suggestion
                    for a double arbitration.<note n="34" xml:id="d319fn34">See League of Nations,
                            <hi rend="italic">Official Journal</hi>, November 1933, p. 1590.</note>
                    It is not likely that Bolivia will accept either plan.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Feely</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
